To make the background image blurry without affecting the inline structure of your current HTML (i.e., without using external stylesheets or breaking inline text styling), you can use a pseudo-background overlay technique with a ::before pseudo-element or by adding a full-screen blurred div behind your content.

Since you're using inline styling and want to keep everything in one file, here's the simplest solution using an additional <div> that creates a blurred background effect:


---

‚úÖ Updated HTML Snippet with Blurry Background:

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>Bootstrap demo</title>
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.6/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.6/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
</head>

<body style="margin: 0; padding: 40px 0; color: #212529; position: relative; min-height: 100vh;">

  <!-- Blurred background layer -->
  <div style="
    background: url('/ThirdSemFinals/ThirdSem_Img/BackgroundAxzel.png') no-repeat center center fixed;
    background-size: cover;
    filter: blur(10px);
    position: fixed;
    top: 0; left: 0;
    width: 100%; height: 100%;
    z-index: -1;
  "></div>

  <!-- Main content -->
  <div style="position: relative; z-index: 1; text-align: center;">
    <img src="/ThirdSemFinals/ThirdSem_Img/Axzel.png" style="
      width: 150px;
      height: 150px;
      object-fit: cover;
      border: 3px solid #9d17eb;
      border-radius: 50%;
    " alt="My Chess Master">

    <h1>Fred Axzel Miano (Axolotl)</h1>

    <div class="Birth">
      <h4><b>Birth:</b></h4>
      <ul type="square">
        <li><h5>July 15 2006</h5></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="Favorites">
      <h4><b>Favorites:</b></h4>
      <ul type="square">
        <li><h5>Valorant</h5></li>
        <li><h5>Rhimson</h5></li>
        <li><h5>Len</h5></li>
        <li><h5>Pork Steak</h5></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="About">
      <h4>About:</h4>
      <h3><pre>  The</pre></h3>
    </div>
  </div>

</body>

</html>


---

üîç Notes:

The <div> with filter: blur(10px); creates the blurred background.

z-index: -1 pushes the blurred background behind all your content.

position: fixed ensures it stays in place behind your scrolling content.


Let me know if you'd like the background to have a slight dark tint for better readability!

